{
  "video_id": "Da-2h2B4faU",
  "title": "String Theory Explained â€“ What is The True Nature of Reality?",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 1479.0,
      "end_time": 4000.0,
      "text": "What is the true nature of the universe?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4600.0,
      "end_time": 6000.0,
      "text": "To answer this question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6000.0,
      "end_time": 8900.0,
      "text": "humans come up with stories to describe the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 9700.0,
      "end_time": 13800.0,
      "text": "We test our stories and learn what to keep and what to throw away."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 14500.0,
      "end_time": 15800.0,
      "text": "But the more we learn,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 15800.0,
      "end_time": 19000.0,
      "text": "the more complicated and weird our stories become."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 19630.0,
      "end_time": 21700.0,
      "text": "Some of them so much so,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21700.0,
      "end_time": 24700.0,
      "text": "that it's really hard to know what they're actually about."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 25200.0,
      "end_time": 26700.0,
      "text": "Like string theory."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 26800.0,
      "end_time": 30500.0,
      "text": "A famous, controversial and often misunderstood story,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 30500.0,
      "end_time": 32300.0,
      "text": "about the nature of everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 32700.000000000004,
      "end_time": 35600.0,
      "text": "Why did we come up with it and is it correct?"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 35600.0,
      "end_time": 38000.0,
      "text": "Or just an idea we should chuck out?"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47700.0,
      "end_time": 49800.0,
      "text": "To understand the true nature of reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 49800.0,
      "end_time": 52300.0,
      "text": "we looked at things up close and were amazed."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 52960.0,
      "end_time": 55000.0,
      "text": "Wonderous landscapes in the dust,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 55000.0,
      "end_time": 57100.0,
      "text": "zoos of bizarre creatures,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 57100.0,
      "end_time": 59000.0,
      "text": "complex protein robots."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59300.0,
      "end_time": 61600.0,
      "text": "All of them made from structures of molecules"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 61600.0,
      "end_time": 64000.0,
      "text": "made up of countless even smaller things:"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 64200.0,
      "end_time": 65000.0,
      "text": "Atoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65600.0,
      "end_time": 68400.0,
      "text": "We thought they were the final layer of reality,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68400.0,
      "end_time": 70700.0,
      "text": "until we smashed them together really hard"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 70700.0,
      "end_time": 73700.0,
      "text": "and discovered things that can't be divided anymore:"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 74020.0,
      "end_time": 75500.0,
      "text": "Elementary particles."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 75900.0,
      "end_time": 77600.0,
      "text": "But now, we had a problem:"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 77800.0,
      "end_time": 80500.0,
      "text": "They are so small that we could no longer look at them."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 81300.0,
      "end_time": 83700.0,
      "text": "Think about it: what is seeing?"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 84200.0,
      "end_time": 87500.0,
      "text": "To see something, we need light, an electromagnetic wave."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 87900.0,
      "end_time": 90000.0,
      "text": "This wave hits the surface of the thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 90000.0,
      "end_time": 92400.0,
      "text": "and gets reflected back from it into your eye."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 93000.0,
      "end_time": 95500.0,
      "text": "The wave carries information from the object"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 95500.0,
      "end_time": 98000.0,
      "text": "that your brain uses to create an image."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 98500.0,
      "end_time": 102000.0,
      "text": "So you can't see something without somehow interacting with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 102400.0,
      "end_time": 106400.0,
      "text": "Seeing is touching, an active process, not a passive one."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 107300.0,
      "end_time": 109280.0,
      "text": "This is not a problem with most things."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 109840.0,
      "end_time": 111000.0,
      "text": "But particles are"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 111000.0,
      "end_time": 111500.0,
      "text": "But particles are very,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 111500.0,
      "end_time": 112000.0,
      "text": "But particles are very, very,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 112000.0,
      "end_time": 113000.0,
      "text": "But particles are very, very, very small."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 113360.0,
      "end_time": 116700.0,
      "text": "So small that the electromagnetic waves we used to see"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 116700.0,
      "end_time": 118300.0,
      "text": "are too big to touch them."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 118600.0,
      "end_time": 120900.0,
      "text": "Visible light just passes over them."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 121600.0,
      "end_time": 124900.0,
      "text": "We can try to solve this by creating electromagnetic waves"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 124900.0,
      "end_time": 127300.0,
      "text": "with more and much smaller wavelengths."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 127400.0,
      "end_time": 130000.0,
      "text": "But more wavelengths, means more energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 130300.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133400.0,
      "text": "So, when we touch a particle with a wave that has a lot of energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 133400.0,
      "end_time": 134800.0,
      "text": "it alters it."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 135000.0,
      "end_time": 137500.0,
      "text": "By looking at a particle, we change it."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 137900.0,
      "end_time": 140900.0,
      "text": "So, we can't measure elementary particles precisely."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 141500.0,
      "end_time": 144700.0,
      "text": "This fact is so important that it has a name:"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 144980.0,
      "end_time": 147400.0,
      "text": "The Heisenberg uncertainty principle."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 147400.0,
      "end_time": 149500.0,
      "text": "The basis of all quantum physics."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 150900.0,
      "end_time": 153200.0,
      "text": "So, what does a particle look like then?"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 153500.0,
      "end_time": 154800.0,
      "text": "What is its nature?"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 155800.0,
      "end_time": 156900.0,
      "text": "We don't know."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 157900.0,
      "end_time": 159300.0,
      "text": "If we look really hard,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 159300.0,
      "end_time": 161600.0,
      "text": "we can see a blurry sphere of influence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 161600.0,
      "end_time": 163600.0,
      "text": "but not the particles themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 163800.0,
      "end_time": 165700.0,
      "text": "We just know they exist."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 166700.0,
      "end_time": 168000.0,
      "text": "But if that's the case,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 168000.0,
      "end_time": 169900.0,
      "text": "how can we do any science with them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 170600.0,
      "end_time": 173700.0,
      "text": "We did what humans do and invented a new story:"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 173700.0,
      "end_time": 175300.0,
      "text": "A mathematical fiction."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 176300.0,
      "end_time": 178200.0,
      "text": "The story of the point particle."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 179000.0,
      "end_time": 182800.0,
      "text": "We decided that we would pretend that a particle is a point in space."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 183100.0,
      "end_time": 187300.0,
      "text": "Any electron is a point with a certain electric charge and a certain mass."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 187500.0,
      "end_time": 189600.0,
      "text": "All indistinguishable from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 189900.0,
      "end_time": 192200.0,
      "text": "This way physicists could define them"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 192200.0,
      "end_time": 194600.0,
      "text": "and calculate all of their interactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 195000.0,
      "end_time": 198700.0,
      "text": "This is called Quantum Field Theory, and solved a lot of problems."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 199200.0,
      "end_time": 202400.0,
      "text": "All of the standard model of particle physics is built on it"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 202400.0,
      "end_time": 204700.0,
      "text": "and it predicts lots of things very well."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 205500.0,
      "end_time": 208000.0,
      "text": "Some quantum properties of the electron for example"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 208000.0,
      "end_time": 210300.0,
      "text": "have been tested and are accurate up to"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 210300.0,
      "end_time": 210800.0,
      "text": "0,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 210800.0,
      "end_time": 211500.0,
      "text": "0,00"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 211500.0,
      "end_time": 212200.0,
      "text": "0,0000"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 212200.0,
      "end_time": 212900.0,
      "text": "0,000000"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 212900.0,
      "end_time": 213600.0,
      "text": "0,00000000"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 213600.0,
      "end_time": 214300.0,
      "text": "0,0000000000"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 214300.0,
      "end_time": 215000.0,
      "text": "0,000000000000"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 215000.0,
      "end_time": 216000.0,
      "text": "0,0000000000002 %."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 216800.0,
      "end_time": 219400.0,
      "text": "So, while particles are not really points,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 219400.0,
      "end_time": 221300.0,
      "text": "by treating them as if they were,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 221300.0,
      "end_time": 223500.0,
      "text": "we get a pretty good picture of the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 224200.0,
      "end_time": 226600.0,
      "text": "Not only did this idea advance science,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 226600.0,
      "end_time": 230500.0,
      "text": "it also led to a lot of real-world technology we use everyday."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 231300.0,
      "end_time": 233000.0,
      "text": "But there's a huge problem:"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 233000.0,
      "end_time": 233800.0,
      "text": "Gravity."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 234400.0,
      "end_time": 238900.0,
      "text": "In quantum mechanics, all physical forces are carried by certain particles."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 239800.0,
      "end_time": 242500.0,
      "text": "But according to Einstein's general relativity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 242500.0,
      "end_time": 245700.0,
      "text": "gravity is not a force like the others in the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 246200.0,
      "end_time": 247900.0,
      "text": "If the universe is a play,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 247900.0,
      "end_time": 249600.0,
      "text": "particles are the actors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 249600.0,
      "end_time": 251700.0,
      "text": "but gravity is the stage."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 252200.0,
      "end_time": 255500.0,
      "text": "To put it simply, gravity is a theory of geometry."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 255600.0,
      "end_time": 257900.0,
      "text": "The geometry of space-time itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 257899.99999999997,
      "end_time": 261599.99999999997,
      "text": "Of distances, which we need to describe with absolute precision."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 262300.0,
      "end_time": 266000.0,
      "text": "But since there is no way to precisely measure things in the quantum world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 266000.0,
      "end_time": 269900.0,
      "text": "our story of gravity doesn't work with our story of quantum physics."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 270400.0,
      "end_time": 275000.0,
      "text": "When physicists tried to add gravity to the story by inventing a new particle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 275200.0,
      "end_time": 277100.0,
      "text": "their mathematics broke down"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 277300.0,
      "end_time": 279000.0,
      "text": "and this is a big problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 279300.0,
      "end_time": 282900.0,
      "text": "If we could marry gravity to quantum physics and the standard model,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 282900.0,
      "end_time": 285100.0,
      "text": "we would have the theory of everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 285700.0,
      "end_time": 288600.0,
      "text": "So, very smart people came up with a new story."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 288700.0,
      "end_time": 291500.0,
      "text": "They asked: What is more complex than a point?"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 292010.0,
      "end_time": 293000.0,
      "text": "A line-"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 293000.0,
      "end_time": 294400.0,
      "text": "A line or a string."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 294500.0,
      "end_time": 296470.0,
      "text": "String theory was born."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 297000.0,
      "end_time": 298900.0,
      "text": "What makes string theory so elegant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 298900.0,
      "end_time": 301800.0,
      "text": "is that it describes many different elementary particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 301800.0,
      "end_time": 304400.0,
      "text": "as different modes of vibration of the string."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 304700.0,
      "end_time": 309000.0,
      "text": "Just like a violin string vibrating differently can give you a lot of different notes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 309000.0,
      "end_time": 311500.0,
      "text": "a string can give you different particles"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 311800.0,
      "end_time": 314600.0,
      "text": "Most importantly, this includes gravity."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 316000.0,
      "end_time": 320200.0,
      "text": "String theory promised to unify all fundamental forces of the universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 320400.0,
      "end_time": 322900.0,
      "text": "This caused enormous excitement and hype."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 323100.0,
      "end_time": 327000.0,
      "text": "String theory quickly graduated to a possible theory of everything"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 327500.0,
      "end_time": 330100.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, string theory comes"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 330100.0,
      "end_time": 332000.0,
      "text": "with a lot of strings attached."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 333400.0,
      "end_time": 336600.0,
      "text": "Much of the maths involving a consistent string theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 336600.0,
      "end_time": 341000.0,
      "text": "does not work in our universe with its three spatial and one temporal dimensions."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 341300.0,
      "end_time": 344600.0,
      "text": "String theory requires ten dimensions to work out."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 344800.0,
      "end_time": 348400.0,
      "text": "So, string theorists did calculations in model universes."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 348800.0,
      "end_time": 353400.0,
      "text": "And then try to get rid of the six additional dimensions and describe our own universe"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 353900.0,
      "end_time": 356100.0,
      "text": "But so far, nobody has succeeded"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 356100.0,
      "end_time": 359500.0,
      "text": "and no prediction of string theory has been proven in an experiment"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 360300.0,
      "end_time": 363700.0,
      "text": "So, string theory did not reveal the nature of our universe."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 364200.0,
      "end_time": 366100.0,
      "text": "One could argue that in this case"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 366100.0,
      "end_time": 368500.0,
      "text": "string theory really isn't useful at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 369010.0,
      "end_time": 372300.0,
      "text": "Science is all about experiments and predictions."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 372300.0,
      "end_time": 373900.0,
      "text": "If we can't do those,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 373900.0,
      "end_time": 375800.0,
      "text": "why should we bother with strings?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 376200.0,
      "end_time": 378600.0,
      "text": "It really is all about how we use it."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 378880.0,
      "end_time": 380700.0,
      "text": "Physics is based on maths."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 380800.0,
      "end_time": 382560.0,
      "text": "Two plus two makes four."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 382900.0,
      "end_time": 385400.0,
      "text": "This is true no matter how you feel about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 385900.0,
      "end_time": 388800.0,
      "text": "And the maths in string theory does work out."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 389000.0,
      "end_time": 391600.0,
      "text": "That's why string theory is still useful."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 392160.0,
      "end_time": 394300.0,
      "text": "Imagine that you want to build a cruise ship,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 394300.0,
      "end_time": 397000.0,
      "text": "but you only have blueprints for a small rowing boat."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 397300.0,
      "end_time": 399000.0,
      "text": "There are plenty of differences:"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 399000.0,
      "end_time": 399900.0,
      "text": "the engine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 399900.0,
      "end_time": 400900.0,
      "text": "the engine, the materials,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 400900.0,
      "end_time": 402000.0,
      "text": "the engine, the materials, the scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 402400.0,
      "end_time": 405000.0,
      "text": "But both things are fundamentally the same:"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 405000.0,
      "end_time": 406400.0,
      "text": "Things that float."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 408000.0,
      "end_time": 410200.0,
      "text": "So, by studying the rowing boat blueprints,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 410200.0,
      "end_time": 413700.0,
      "text": "you might still learn something about how to build a cruise ship eventually."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 414400.0,
      "end_time": 415500.0,
      "text": "With string theory,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 415500.0,
      "end_time": 418400.0,
      "text": "we can try to answer some questions about quantum gravity"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 418400.0,
      "end_time": 420800.0,
      "text": "that have been puzzling physicists for decades."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 420800.0,
      "end_time": 422400.0,
      "text": "Such as how black holes work"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 422400.0,
      "end_time": 424000.0,
      "text": "or the information paradox."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 424400.0,
      "end_time": 427000.0,
      "text": "String theory may point us in the right direction."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 427400.0,
      "end_time": 428800.0,
      "text": "When used in this spirit,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 428800.0,
      "end_time": 432500.0,
      "text": "string theory becomes a precious tool for theoretical physicists"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 432500.0,
      "end_time": 435400.0,
      "text": "and help them discover new aspects of the quantum world"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 435400.0,
      "end_time": 437500.0,
      "text": "and some beautiful mathematics."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 437800.0,
      "end_time": 440000.0,
      "text": "So, maybe the story of string theory"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 440000.0,
      "end_time": 442000.0,
      "text": "is not the theory of everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 442200.0,
      "end_time": 444600.0,
      "text": "But just like the story of the point particle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 444600.0,
      "end_time": 447000.0,
      "text": "it may be an extremely useful story."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 447500.0,
      "end_time": 450400.0,
      "text": "We don't yet know what the true nature of reality is"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 450400.0,
      "end_time": 453200.0,
      "text": "but we'll keep coming up with stories to try and find out."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 453300.0,
      "end_time": 454600.0,
      "text": "Until one day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 454600.0,
      "end_time": 455600.0,
      "text": "Until one day, hopefully"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 455600.0,
      "end_time": 456800.0,
      "text": "Until one day, hopefully, we do know."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 458230.0,
      "end_time": 461500.0,
      "text": "This video was supported by the Swiss National Science Foundation"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 461500.0,
      "end_time": 464900.0,
      "text": "and realized with the scientific advice of Alessandro Sfondrini."
    }
  ]
}